modules.description: This module defines configuration options for rendering structured data as Markdown, controlling the visual style and formatting of lists, trees, tables, and preformatted text. It supports customizing how vertical and horizontal lists are displayed, whether trees are foldable or unfolded, and the style of preformatted text using code blocks or inline quotes. Concrete use cases include adjusting output for readability with `default` or lightweight rendering with `uniform`, and configuring tab width or quotation/table framing styles.

This module renders structured data into Markdown format, supporting customizable output for lists, trees, tables, and preformatted text. It works with `PrintBox.t` values and uses `Config.t` to control visual formatting aspects like indentation, line breaks, and block styles. Concrete use cases include generating readable Markdown documentation from in-memory data structures and exporting formatted tables with user-defined borders and alignment.
